The paper proposes a toolkit for automatically building skills for virtual assistants using structured data from websites. This involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of structured data suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB).
